This article provides a list of individuals who were invited to sit in the First Lady's box at the State of the Union Address. Some notable guests include Gary and Robert Allen, who used funds from the Recovery Act to launch a new business; Ursula M. Burns, the CEO of Xerox Corporation; Amy Chyao, a high school student who developed a new cancer treatment; Kendra Baker and Zachary Davis, who opened an organic ice cream shop with the help of a Recovery Act loan; Brandon Fisher, who helped rescue trapped Chilean miners; Brandon Ford, a high school student involved in building fuel-efficient vehicles; and the Green family, who lost their daughter in the Tucson shooting. Other guests include military personnel, educators, and business owners who have benefited from government programs.